# [NMOP](../wg/nmop.html)

## Summary

The NMOP (Network Management Operations) Working Group met at IETF 126 to discuss its active drafts, recent hackathon developments, and the path forward for its core initiatives. Key highlights included progress on the YANG-Push to Message Broker integration, Network Incident and Anomaly Management suites, and a structured discussion on the modeling approaches for SIMAP (Service-to-Infrastructure Mapping). The working group reached a clear path forward on SIMAP modeling via a formal session poll, opting to support both RFC 8345-based and RFC 8795-based approaches depending on the specific operational use cases. Additionally, opportunities for collaboration between NMOP and the Network Management Research Group (NMRG) were explored.

